# Poem

In the hush of dawn’s first light,
Code awakens, soft and bright.
Between the lines, a quiet spark,
A tiny star within the dark.

Footsteps of the day begin,
Winds of wonder drift within.
Every keystroke, brief and small,
Builds a world that dreams to call.

So let the page hold rhythm true,
A little verse in morning blue.
Markdown sings, plain and free,
A simple song in README.
